cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with object detection and learning from visual information.
2. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper involves using subtitles as a source of information for learning object detectors.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper proposes a weakly supervised learning algorithm for object detection.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with learning from both visual and linguistic information.
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category as the paper involves mining a training set from a large corpus of documentary films.
